subSubSection.paragraph:
Receptacle uniseriate, consisting of a row of 3–28(–43) cells. Most of the appendage cells give rise to 1–2 corner cells that function as simple antheridia in young thalli. Perithecium with a broad, ovoidal venter and an abruptly distinguished, straight and slender neck. [Detailed descriptions: 
Thaxter 1908
; 
Majewski 1994b
; 
Weir 1994
; 
Santamaria 2003
; 
De Kesel 2010
]

